Description:
(Cross-listed with CLAS 51304) Major works of Latin literature, studied in their historical context by genre;
 knowledge of Latin not required. Authors read include Plautus, Terence, Lucretius, Cicero, Catullus, Vergil,
 Horace, Petronius, Seneca, Suetonius, Tacitus and Juvenal.

